*** NickServ Help - Command: RESETPASS ***
Resets the password of a nickname.

This command is used together with SENDPASS. A helper or
services operator starts the password reset with SENDPASS
nick: an authorization code is then sent by E-Mail to the
address registered for the nickname, along with further
instructions.

Once you receive the reset code by E-Mail, use RESETPASS
to set a new password. The new password must be at least
5 characters long, must not contain spaces or control
codes, and must not be the same as the nickname.

The reset code is valid for 7 days. After that the request
expires and a fresh SENDPASS is needed.

You do NOT need to be identified to the nickname to run
this command: being able to receive E-Mail at the address
tied to the nickname is the proof of ownership.

To cancel a pending password reset request, contact a
services operator to run AUTHRESET RESETPASS on the nick.

Syntax:

/ns RESETPASS nickname code new-password

Example:
/ns RESETPASS SuperPicci 1234567 n3wP4ssw0rd

Type /join #IRCHelp for more information.
*** End of Help ***
